nhc_headline: ...JERRY A LITTLE STRONGER... ...EXPECTED TO PASS VERY NEAR THE NORTHERN LEEWARD ISLANDS LATE THURSDAY AND THURSDAY NIGHT...
summary: ...JERRY A LITTLE STRONGER... ...EXPECTED TO PASS VERY NEAR THE NORTHERN LEEWARD ISLANDS LATE THURSDAY AND THURSDAY NIGHT... As of 11:00 AM AST Wed Oct 08 the center of Jerry was located near 13.9, -52.7 with movement WNW at 23 mph. The minimum central pressure was 1003 mb with maximum sustained winds of about 60 mph.
